<div id="review_1745789597" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1745789597" />
    <a title="Amanda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7897151-amanda"><img alt="Amanda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1461450073p2/7897151.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1745789597?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amanda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amanda" href="/user/show/7897151-amanda">Amanda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8201596-sugar">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7897151-amanda?shelf=black-literature">black-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1745789597" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14381562184954396076">Bernice L. McFadden&apos;s Sugar is a novel about finding your place in the world and in the family you create for yourself. It takes place in 1955 Arkansas, when Sugar, a vivacious and unapologetic sex worker, moves to the small, Christian town of Bigelow. Her next door neighbor, Pearl, is drawn to her, partly because Sugar resembles her teenage daughter who was brutally murdered 15 years ago. <br/><br/>I was amazed at the characterization McFadden was able to achieve in such a short, quick-moving book. While</span>
  <span id="freeText14381562184954396076" style="display:none">Bernice L. McFadden's Sugar is a novel about finding your place in the world and in the family you create for yourself. It takes place in 1955 Arkansas, when Sugar, a vivacious and unapologetic sex worker, moves to the small, Christian town of Bigelow. Her next door neighbor, Pearl, is drawn to her, partly because Sugar resembles her teenage daughter who was brutally murdered 15 years ago. <br /><br />I was amazed at the characterization McFadden was able to achieve in such a short, quick-moving book. While I thought the development of Pearl and Sugar's friendship was a bit rushed, I came to care about their relationship and about them as individuals. I loved learning about Sugar's childhood and early adulthood, as harrowing as it was. The side characters were fully developed, and we were given glimpses into their backgrounds, as well. <br /><br />While this book carries darkness throughout - it starts with the murder of Pearl's daughter, Jude - I was shocked by the events of the climax of the novel (trigger warnings for rape and gore). I was also perplexed by the ending, which was multitudinous. Overall, though, I fully believed these characters were real people and am invested in their lives. I will be reading the sequel, This Bitter Earth.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14381562184954396076" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

